node.text: Anyone else take their pal every where you go? Feels like I can count on one hand the times I’ve left Maddie at home ✨

Right around this time last year my dear friend Maddie was diagnosed with cancer, it was one of those moments you start trying to make bargains with the universe, somehow thinking life is off schedule. But today the good news is that my dear speckled friend is healthy, running hard, enjoying life like only dogs can do. And likely most important we now know that today is enough. It’s what we’ve been given and all is on schedule ✨

It’s gonna be a such a good winter out in Montana with my best friend ✨ #ad #IAMS dog food makes it easy to give Maddie a breakfast she loves with good grains for healthy energy to keep her by my side all day – because we’re both happiest in the snow. Check out the link in my bio for more on the connection between dog and human health from the good folks over at @IAMS. #IAMSWhoIAm
Ain’t these two the cutest ever ⛄️
Never would of figured I’d love kayaking in the cold so much, lovely and quiet ⛄️

Life is better when we share it with dogs #ad IAMS dog food has the right grains and high-quality protein that help keep Maddie healthy and active. When she’s healthy, I’m less stressed which means I’m healthier too. The nice folks over at @IAMS recently shared an article about the connection between dog and human health, and it’s a good read (link in bio) #IAMS #IAMSWhoIAm
Maddie would like to let everyone know her nose is covered w/ snow

Annual Montana self portrait ✨⁣
⁣
One of my recent joys has been cutting fire wood for the season. For $5/cord anyone can enter our beautiful National Forests, fell a dead tree, and spend time connecting to nature and your heat source for the season. It helps to thin the forest and provides new space for life to begin again 🌲

Old trucks & good boots w/ @blundstoneusa ⁣
⁣
If you’ve been on the fence about stomping around in a pair of these boots they have a real fair deal going on over on their website today, find it through their IG account. We wear em everyday and love em ✨
Decorating doors & dogs today, def my fav time of year ✨🎄
Sometimes when we’re way out in places like this I think of all the folks grinding through traffic in LA. It’s not lost on me how blessed we are to be able to make out a life going to places I adore

There’re just some things about me that will never change. I’ll always be torn between my beloved Tennessee and wild Montana, grateful I get to live it and see places from the movies I watched growing up ✨
My favorite Maddie move ✨
Some days it’s more beautiful when you can’t see to the mountain tops ✨
Bit more winter showed up ❄️
Maddie & @jaredchambers

Chatting with the locals ✨ if home made me anything its loving a dirt road. ⁣
⁣
I’ve hung my hat a lot of places in the states, LA to Savannah, and for my dollar there ain’t nothing better than wide open country. A man could live a good life in a place like this.
New winter jacket 🐻
The call is is to simply be who we are and to love being that ✨
Step 11, mediations before the snow comes
I figure someday we’ll be snowbirds but for now a little winter alpine fly fishing is so dang charming ✨

Always digs camping in the quiet in between seasons ✨and hopefully my little kayak is showing up this weekend! These’s a whole bunch of backcountry stuff I wanna paddle out towards see before the full on snow comes

Been adventuring around for months with @BlundstoneUSA and were still lovin' em. Got an easy link to them in my stories today if you're looking for a pair to cover your own feets #sponsored -
I also wanna quickly say it’s a huge blessing and honor to get hired to shoot and create for brands, but I also adore these boots and I’m a huge fan. Worth a try for sure ✨
If Maddie ever releases a country album I got her cover dialed ✨
